reviewText:
The movie "Death of a Cheerleader" was a great movie.  Tori Spelling's acting was great.  But the girl who played the murderer was poorly cast.  She looked way too cute to accurately portray her role.  With some makeup, they could have make her look more believable.
The other movie "Deadly Pursuits" was just....good.  Again, Tori Spelling's acting was great.  Not so much her co-star.

I always liked Tori Spelling in all her movies. She's plays the perfect snob.
It was a real good movie.
Mrs Glenn Bouley
Thank you so very much and your generosity and hospitality is greatly appreciated. God bless you and your family!
